11 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act;
allowing members of a public body to participate in a
12 meeting from their private residence under certain
circumstances; excluding private residences from
13 location disclosure under certain circumstances;
clarifying applicability; defining term; clarifying
14 compliance requirements; stating legislative intent;
providing for codification; and providing an
15 effective date.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 307.2 of Title 25, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. A member of a public body may participate in a public
23 meeting via videoconference or teleconference from the private
24 residence of the member, and shall not be required to disclose the
