1 addr ess of the private residence on the meeting notice or agenda,
2 provided the following conditions are met:
3 1. The member identifies the location as the "private
4 residence" on the meeting notice and agenda, without further detail;
5 2. The videoconference or teleconference technology used allows
6 the public to see and hear the member during the meeting; and
7 3. The member's participation from his or her private residence
8 does not restrict or limit public access to the meeting or the
9 member's contributions to the meeting.
10 B. This section does not apply when a public body holds a
11 meeting entirely or primarily at a member's private residence, or
12 when two or more members are present at a member's private
13 residence. In such cases, full disclosure of the meeting location
14 is required under the existing provisions of the Oklahoma Open
15 Meeting Act.
16 C. For purposes of this section, "private residence" means any
17 home, apartment, or other personal living space that is not used as
18 a public or commercial meeting site.
19 D. Public bodies shall ensure compliance with all other
20 provisions of the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act, including transparency,
21 accessibility, and notice requirements, when implementing this
22 section.
23 E. It is the Legislature's intent to balance the principles of
24 open governance with the privacy and security of individuals
